seg.seg:
Quin hi quoque, religioni
                                Christianae qui non assentiunt, neminem tamen absterrent, nullum
                                oppugnant imbutum;

Caeterum ut hortari atque
                                admonere lllorum est, ita coercere atque in facinorosos
                                animaduertere prineipis atque aliorum est magistra­tuum;

uincentibus suis decurrunt in
                                aciem, saeuientesque in profligatos inhibent uidisse tantum atque
                                appel­lasse praesentes ad uitam satis;

Nam alibi, quotus quisque est
                                qui nesciat, nisi quid seorsum prospiciat sibi, quantumuis florente
                                Republica semet tamen fame periturum;

haec ne Dea quidem fieri
                                uellet, nullis relictis miseris, quibus imperare atque insultare
                                possit;

Therfore al this matter he
                                lefte vndiscussed, and gaue to euery man free libertie and choyse to
                                beleue what he woulde;

But as it is their offyce to
                                gyue good exhortations and cownsell, so it is the deuty of the
                                prince and the other magistrates to correct and punnyshe offenders;

Whyche ennemyes, yf they do
                                but see them and speake to them, yt ys ynoughe for the sauegarde of
                                theyr lyues;

She wold not by her good
                                will be made a goddes, if there were no wretches left, whom she
                                might be lady ouer to mocke and scorne;
